---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — DocArmor by Katafract"
  description="DocArmor privacy policy. Your encrypted documents never leave your device. AES-256 encryption, Face ID protection, no cloud sync."
  ogDescription="DocArmor collects zero data. Your documents are AES-256 encrypted and locked behind Face ID. Nothing ever leaves your device."
  section="prose"
>
  <link slot="head" rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css" />


    <div class="prose-header">
      <p class="prose-eyebrow">DocArmor &mdash; Privacy Policy</p>
      <h1>DocArmor Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="prose-meta">Katafract LLC &mdash; Last updated March 2026 &mdash; <a href="//privacy">All app policies &rarr;</a></p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-body">

      <div class="callout">
        <p>DocArmor stores your most sensitive documents — IDs, insurance cards, passports — encrypted with AES-256 and locked behind Face ID or Touch ID. Nothing is ever uploaded, synced to iCloud, or transmitted anywhere. Your documents exist only on your device.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>What Data Does DocArmor Collect?</h2>
      <p>None. DocArmor does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data whatsoever.</p>

      <table class="data-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Data Type</th>
            <th>Collected?</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Document images (IDs, cards, etc.)</td>
            <td><span class="badge-never">Never</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Document text or OCR content</td>
            <td><span class="badge-never">Never</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Biometric data (Face ID / Touch ID)</td>
            <td><span class="badge-never">Never</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Encryption keys</td>
            <td><span class="badge-never">Never</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Device identifiers (IDFA, etc.)</td>
            <td><span class="badge-never">Never</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Usage analytics</td>
            <td><span class="badge-never">Never</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Crash logs</td>
            <td><span class="badge-never">Never</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Account or login information</td>
            <td><span class="badge-never">Never</span></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Document Storage and Encryption</h2>
      <p>All documents you add to DocArmor are encrypted using <strong>AES-256</strong> via Apple's CryptoKit framework before being written to the app's private local storage container. The encryption key is generated on your device, stored in the iOS Keychain with the highest available protection class, and never leaves your device.</p>
      <p>Documents are stored in the app's sandboxed private directory and are not accessible to any other app or to the operating system without authentication.</p>

      <h2>Face ID and Touch ID</h2>
      <p>DocArmor uses Apple's Local Authentication framework (LAContext) to require biometric verification before granting access to your documents. Your biometric data — fingerprints, face geometry — is never accessed or read by DocArmor. The framework returns only a pass/fail result. Biometric data never leaves the device's Secure Enclave.</p>

      <h2>Document Scanner</h2>
      <p>The built-in document scanner uses Apple's VisionKit framework (VNDocumentCameraViewController) and processes the camera feed entirely on-device. Scanned document images are passed directly to the encryption pipeline — they are never written to your photo library, never cached to disk in unencrypted form, and never transmitted anywhere.</p>

      <h2>iCloud and Sync</h2>
      <p>DocArmor explicitly disables iCloud sync for all document data. Your encrypted vault does not appear in iCloud Drive, iCloud Backup, or any Apple cloud service. Documents exist only in local device storage. <strong>If you delete the app, your documents are permanently deleted.</strong> We recommend exporting documents you need before uninstalling.</p>

      <h2>Photo Library Access</h2>
      <p>If you choose to import an existing photo from your library into DocArmor, the app requests photo library read access for that operation only. The imported image is immediately encrypted and stored in the local vault. DocArmor does not scan, index, or retain access to your broader photo library.</p>

      <h2>In-App Purchases</h2>
      <p>DocArmor is a one-time purchase processed entirely by Apple through the App Store. We do not receive or store your payment information, Apple ID, or any billing details. Purchase verification is handled on-device by Apple's StoreKit framework.</p>

      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>DocArmor does not integrate with any third-party analytics services, advertising networks, social media SDKs, cloud storage providers, or data brokers. There are no third-party frameworks in the app that collect or transmit data.</p>

      <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>DocArmor does not collect personal information from anyone, including children under 13. The app is rated 4+ and is safe for all ages.</p>

      <h2>Data Retention</h2>
      <p>All document data is stored locally on your device. We retain nothing on our end because nothing is ever sent to us. Uninstalling the app permanently and irrecoverably deletes all stored documents — there is no server-side copy to restore from.</p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>If we ever change this privacy policy, we will update this page with the new date. Since we don't collect email addresses or contact information, we cannot notify you directly &mdash; please check this page periodically.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>If you have questions about this privacy policy or DocArmor's privacy practices, please reach out:</p>
      <div class="contact-card">
        <h3>Privacy Inquiries</h3>
        <p>Katafract LLC</p>
        <p><a href="mailto:privacy@katafract.com">privacy@katafract.com</a></p>
        <p>We typically respond within one business day.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  
</Base>
